modules.description: Performs numerical computations including matrix operations, statistical functions, and linear algebra routines. Operates on arrays, matrices, and tensors with support for various numerical types. Used for tasks such as gradient descent in machine learning models and solving differential equations in engineering simulations.

Provides functions to manage and execute Zoo scripts and gists, including uploading, downloading, updating, and evaluating code. Operates on strings representing gist IDs, file paths, and OCaml expressions. Enables running scripts with arguments, inspecting gist details, and navigating gist storage locations.

Provides functions to construct and manipulate file paths, including extending a base path with identifiers and creating temporary directories. Works with strings representing file system paths and Unix file permissions. Used to generate unique paths for temporary files and organize data in structured directories.

Checks if a specific gist version exists, updates records with new versions, and removes all versions of a gist. Retrieves the latest remote version and timestamp for a gist, and parses structured gist strings into component parts including version, time tolerance, and pin status. Operates on strings representing gist IDs and versions, and floats for timestamps.

Adds the "zoo" directive to the OCaml toploop, enabling interactive exploration of numerical algorithms. Works with OCaml's toploop environment and associated runtime structures. Allows developers to dynamically load and test Owl's numerical modules during interactive sessions.
